    "alternate_descriptions": {
        "auditory": "Someone's voice drops to something quieter and more measured—words chosen carefully, responses brief, sentences that leave space between them like stepping stones. They listen with focus, letting silence do work where they might normally fill it, and when they do speak, each word feels weighed before release.",
        "tactile": "The tension pools in their shoulders and jaw—not the sharp spike of panic but a sustained pressure, muscles held deliberately taut like a bowstring at half-draw. The air around them feels compressed, their presence somehow smaller, pulled inward. Each movement carries a quality of controlled release, like they're measuring out their reactions in careful doses.",
